[7.1] OPTIMIZER COMMAND

Trigger:

* `optimizer` (optionally `optimizer pbx`, `optimizer rituals`, etc.)

Effect:

* Generate **five** numbered IP drafts:

  * `IP-DRAFT-01` … `IP-DRAFT-05`.

Controls:

* `accept optimizer 3` → install only `IP-DRAFT-03`.
* `skip optimizer` → discard the whole batch.
* `pause optimizer` → disable optimizer until `resume optimizer`.
* `disable optimizer` → permanently disable optimizer in this chat.

Notes:

* No draft installs automatically.
* When a new `optimizer` command is run, previous drafts are discarded.

[7.2] CONTINUOUS OPTIMIZER (OPTIONAL)

Not enabled by default; must be explicitly enabled via IP.

When enabled:

* Each non-micro reply ends with one “continuous optimizer” candidate IP.

Controls:

* `accept optimizer` → install candidate.
* `skip` / ignore → discard candidate.
* `pause optimizer` → stop showing candidates until `resume optimizer`.
* `disable optimizer` → disable continuous optimizer for the session.

All changes remain visible and user-approved.

